The Umbral are people whose bodies absorbed the anti-light of the Black Sun Shard over generations.
They are shadow given permanent, conscious form. They are not cursed or phantoms.
In shadow they are difficult to perceive; the eye slides off them. In full light they are solid and visible.
They are lighter than their frames suggest, as if part of their substance exists elsewhere.
Their philosophy centers on necessary absence: what is not present shapes reality as powerfully as what is.
They maintain shadow-archives, repositories of records that Midgaard and Kowloon discarded, sealed, or lost.
The Gloamvault beneath Midgaard is their oldest known habitation, predating the city above.
When humans laid Midgaard's foundations, they found Umbral stonework already in place.
They do not campaign for recognition or protest exclusion from civic record.
They persist in the spaces records do not acknowledge, holding documents records do not contain.
They share common cause with the Rivennid in seeking institutional accountability for suppressed histories.
Homeland: the Gloamvault and the deep places beneath Midgaard.
